00:09:18.304 --> 00:09:21.864
well as the expression profiles that differentiate the mutant

161
00:09:21.904 --> 00:09:25.674
cells from the wild type. So we also

162
00:09:25.684 --> 00:09:29.544
performed FACS sorting so that we can enrich the data with the cell

163
00:09:29.664 --> 00:09:33.144
types identified in the multi-omics platform.

164
00:09:34.124 --> 00:09:35.964
And this

165
00:09:37.604 --> 00:09:41.524
new profile technique is called single-cell Kinex

166
00:09:41.564 --> 00:09:45.224
by Pek Bao, and we have been using this for several of the

167
00:09:45.244 --> 00:09:46.104
survivorship

168
00:09:47.004 --> 00:09:47.564
samples.

169
00:09:48.564 --> 00:09:52.484
So this is one of them that we were able to show

170
00:09:52.504 --> 00:09:54.004
the clustering of these

171
00:09:54.864 --> 00:09:56.764
from the full-length RNA-Seq

172
00:09:57.624 --> 00:10:00.504
into different groups, and the mutant cells were indeed

173
00:10:01.524 --> 00:10:05.344
clustered and were only present in two

174
00:10:05.384 --> 00:10:07.224
clusters. And using the

175
00:10:09.204 --> 00:10:12.504
kind of candidate markers, we were able to show that this is

176
00:10:13.204 --> 00:10:16.164
highly enriched in CD8 memory T cells.

177
00:10:16.784 --> 00:10:20.184
And more in-depth study presented in Nadia's poster.

178
00:10:20.314 --> 00:10:24.084
So if you want to see how these mutant cells

179
00:10:24.404 --> 00:10:28.284
track in the T cell differentiation lineage, go to

180
00:10:28.324 --> 00:10:29.984
her poster on Tuesday.

181
00:10:32.184 --> 00:10:34.984
So throughout these analysis, what we found is that

182
00:10:36.244 --> 00:10:39.804
the chemotherapies the pediatric cancer patients

183
00:10:40.184 --> 00:10:44.104
received 20 or 30 years ago can have an

184
00:10:44.164 --> 00:10:47.944
imprint on the blood cells when they become the adult.

185
00:10:48.364 --> 00:10:49.394
And in the case of the

186
00:10:50.764 --> 00:10:54.264
STAT3 mutant cells, we found it leads to clonal

187
00:10:54.544 --> 00:10:58.504
expansion of specific subtypes of T cells and leading

188
00:10:58.564 --> 00:10:58.764
to

189
00:10:59.924 --> 00:11:01.544
potential malfunction of

190
00:11:02.424 --> 00:11:04.184
