194
00:11:16.804 --> 00:11:19.244
And this is a study in collaboration, Dr.

195
00:11:19.584 --> 00:11:23.424
Sam Brady from Pharmacyuk Science, and Greg Armstrong

196
00:11:23.824 --> 00:11:27.764
from Epidemiology and Cancer Control, who's also the leader of

197
00:11:28.344 --> 00:11:30.224
a childhood cancer survivorship study.

198
00:11:30.694 --> 00:11:34.084
And I want to mention that we are very fortunate to be selected

199
00:11:34.524 --> 00:11:38.054
for simultaneous publication for cancer discovery,

200
00:11:38.724 --> 00:11:39.614
and this

201
00:11:40.864 --> 00:11:44.804
is a QR code, and if you scan it, this paper

202
00:11:44.884 --> 00:11:46.844
is hot right on the internet,

203
00:11:48.444 --> 00:11:49.624
right as moment being

204
00:11:49.684 --> 00:11:53.372
released.So the secondary

205
00:11:53.412 --> 00:11:56.992
neoplasm cohort from CCSS, we have

206
00:11:57.472 --> 00:11:58.972
include 200

207
00:12:00.792 --> 00:12:04.632
FLP samples from 159 patients. Most of these, we

208
00:12:04.672 --> 00:12:08.032
were able to get good quality whole genome or exome

